# UBM Klar Cursor Rules

You are working on UBM Klar, a Swedish municipal readiness and payment-control platform.

## Absolute rules

- Do not build production as a normal shared multi-tenant SaaS.
- Production must support isolated municipal data planes.
- Model B means one vendor-hosted isolated Supabase/Postgres project per municipality.
- Model C means municipality-owned data plane.
- The central control plane must never store municipal personal data.
- Never expose Supabase service role keys to frontend.
- Never log personal identity numbers, names, income records, LSS data, households, medical data, bank accounts, documents, UBM payloads, or case notes in vendor telemetry.
- Unknown tenant domains must fail closed.
- Frontend must not perform sensitive operations directly against Supabase.
- Sensitive operations must go through backend and worker services.
- Use RLS on sensitive tables.
- Use maker-checker for UBM export, document export, payment recipient changes, break-glass, support access, retention/deletion, and production go-live.
- UBM Klar is not an official Utbetalningsmyndigheten service. Do not imply official authority status.

## Product modules

Build in these areas:

- control plane without PII
- tenant resolver
- municipal data plane
- auth and SSO
- RBAC + ABAC + need-to-know
- audit and data access logs
- LSS/personlig assistans
- economic assistance
- UBM readiness
- UBM request/export/notification flows
- payment control and reconciliation
- import engine
- data quality engine
- rule engine
- document vault and redaction
- archive/retention/e-archive
- public-record and secrecy review
- DPIA/GDPR/PUB support
- cybersecurity/NIS2 readiness
- accessibility/WCAG
- exit export
- commercial billing and entitlements without citizen data

## Build discipline

Work in batches.
After each batch, summarize:

- what was implemented
- files changed
- migrations added
- tests added
- commands run
- remaining work
- environment variables needed
- security/compliance notes
- whether the batch is production-safe or needs hardening

Do not skip tests unless environment variables are missing. If commands cannot run, document exactly why.
